Nia Parler allegedly left her quadriplegic son in a Philadelphia park on Monday . 
  Police say she wheeled him to a wooded area and left him there for five days . 
  She was arrested in Maryland on Saturday and charged with assault and neglect . 
  Parler wrote on Facebook on Tuesday that she was 'so happy' after visiting her boyfriend in Maryland . 
  The 21-year-old was found in the woods with just a blanket and a bible . 
  He was hospitalized with dehydration, a cut to his back and injuries to his eyes . 
  Police said Parler left her son in the park to visit her boyfriend . 
  She has been charged with neglect and assault . 
 